# Contributing Guidelines

We appreciate your interest in contributing to [Project Name]! To maintain a welcoming and collaborative environment, please follow these guidelines when contributing to the project:

## Code of Conduct

Before contributing, review and adhere to our [Code of Conduct](CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md).

## How to Contribute

1. Fork the repository to your GitHub account.
2. Create a new branch from the `main` branch for each new feature or fix you work on.
3. Make your changes and commit them with a clear and descriptive message.
4. Push your branch to your forked repository.
5. Submit a pull request to the `main` branch of the original repository.
6. Be prepared to participate in the code review process and make necessary changes.

## Style Guidelines

[Include any specific style guidelines or conventions relevant to your project]

## Reporting Issues

If you encounter any problems or have suggestions for improvements, please open an issue on GitHub. Provide a clear title and description for the issue, including steps to reproduce (if applicable).

Thank you for contributing to [Project Name]!
